1
00:00:04,605 --> 00:00:07,541
(Luna) I want to be Ryoko's friend who lied to me.

2
00:00:07,608 --> 00:00:10,544
(Ryoko) I thought we were friends for a long time.

3
00:00:10,611 --> 00:00:16,050
⟨Luna and Ryoko deepened their bond through their trip to Osaka and became true buddies⟩

4
00:00:16,117 --> 00:00:21,055
⟨However, the shadow of a new incident hangs over these two...⟩

5
00:00:21,122 --> 00:00:24,058
(Ryoko) I guess we're friends now.

6
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:27,061
⟨Ryoko is with her former best friend...⟩

7
00:00:27,128 --> 00:00:31,565
(Luna) My existence was denied and I had no place to belong.

8
00:00:31,632 --> 00:00:37,071
⟨And Luna ends up confronting her father with whom she has a feud⟩

9
00:00:37,138 --> 00:00:42,143
⟨The second act of “Moonlight Journey” begins in Tokyo⟩

10
00:00:47,648 --> 00:00:51,085
(Luna) Hmm... (Bubbly) Are you still worried?

11
00:00:51,152 --> 00:00:53,587
(Bubbly) I think it's wonderful.

12
00:00:53,654 --> 00:00:57,591
(Luna) I think a more calm tone would be nice.

13
00:00:57,658 --> 00:00:59,093
(sound of door opening)

14
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:02,596
(Ryoko) Hello! (Luna) Ryoko, welcome.

15
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:04,532
(Ryoko) What?

16
00:01:04,598 --> 00:01:08,035
(Luna) Currently, opinions are divided over the color of the walls regarding the renovation plans for the store.

17
00:01:08,102 --> 00:01:12,039
(Ryoko) Ah, there's also an overall balance.

18
00:01:12,106 --> 00:01:17,044
>> Yes, please wait! Marky Moon's special meal.

19
00:01:17,111 --> 00:01:20,047
(Ryoko) Ah, Tamura-san! (Tamura) Ah, hello.

20
00:01:20,114 --> 00:01:24,552
(Ryoko) I see! You've been in Tokyo since April. Have you gotten used to it yet?

21
00:01:24,618 --> 00:01:26,053
(Tamura) Well, somehow.

22
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,557
>> I didn't know that the police had dispatch training.

23
00:01:29,623 --> 00:01:33,627
Eat heartily and gain power! (Tamura) Itadakimasu.

24
00:01:37,631 --> 00:01:39,567
(Tamura) Delicious. >> Alright!

25
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:42,570
(Ryoko) We also simmered the stew for 4 hours tonight.

26
00:01:42,636 --> 00:01:46,574
>> Wow~ It took 3 hours and 18 minutes for me to lose.

27
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:51,078
📱(vibration sound)

28
00:01:51,145 --> 00:01:53,581
(Ryoko) Atsushi What happened?

29
00:01:53,647 --> 00:01:55,583
(Atsushi) The light bulb in the bathroom went out.

30
00:01:55,649 --> 00:01:58,085
📱 There's (Ryoko) stock on the kitchen shelf, right?

31
00:01:58,152 --> 00:01:59,587
(Atsushi) No.

32
00:01:59,653 --> 00:02:01,589
(Ryoko) Then go buy some.

33
00:02:01,655 --> 00:02:04,525
📱 I don't know how many watts it is. (Ryoko) Hmm.

34
00:02:04,592 --> 00:02:08,028
(Kikuo) I'm home~ >> Ah, dad is back.

35
00:02:08,095 --> 00:02:09,530
(Kikuo) Huh?

36
00:02:09,597 --> 00:02:11,532
📱(Sound of disconnected call)

37
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:16,537
(Ryoko) Huh~ Please don't call me with the light bulb in the bathroom anymore.

38
00:02:16,604 --> 00:02:19,540
(Tamura) Something about it makes me smile. It's so peaceful.

39
00:02:19,607 --> 00:02:21,542
(Ryoko) Well.

40
00:02:21,609 --> 00:02:23,544
⟨After a trip to Osaka→

41
00:02:23,611 --> 00:02:27,548
I started to cherish everyday life⟩

42
00:02:27,615 --> 00:02:29,550
⟨Thanks to mom⟩

43
00:02:29,617 --> 00:02:31,552
Thank you mama.

44
00:02:31,619 --> 00:02:35,556
>> No, I don't know...

45
00:02:35,623 --> 00:02:38,058
(Aromatic) I'm home. (Kikuo) Welcome back!

46
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:42,062
Fragrance Do you know how many watts the light bulb in the bathroom is?

47
00:02:42,129 --> 00:02:44,565
Just look at what's written on the light bulb.

48
00:02:44,632 --> 00:02:48,068
(2 people) Ah~｡ >> Huh~｡

49
00:02:48,135 --> 00:02:52,072
I'm tired from my part-time job, so don't ask me nonsense.

50
00:02:52,139 --> 00:02:54,074
I see.

51
00:02:54,141 --> 00:02:57,077
I'm hungry.

52
00:02:57,144 --> 00:02:59,146
(Sniffing sound) Huh.

53
00:03:08,589 --> 00:03:11,025
(Meguru) Welcome!

54
00:03:11,091 --> 00:03:14,528
(Ryoko) What!? Mr. Kominato! (Kominato) It's been a while.

55
00:03:14,595 --> 00:03:17,531
(Luna) When will you come to Tokyo? (Ryoko) Are you on a business trip?

56
00:03:17,598 --> 00:03:21,535
>> No, I left Osaka and came here.

57
00:03:21,602 --> 00:03:23,604
(Ryoko) Huh! (Luna) Huh!

58
00:03:25,105 --> 00:03:27,041
"Temporary staffing company".

59
00:03:27,107 --> 00:03:29,543
>> I started it with two friends.

60
00:03:29,610 --> 00:03:32,046
(Luna) Have you started your own business? >> Yes.

61
00:03:32,112 --> 00:03:36,050
(Ryoko) Detective: You took the plunge by quitting your job.

62
00:03:36,116 --> 00:03:38,552
>>People: I don't like living with doubts.

63
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:41,555
If I was going to start my life over again, now would be the time.

64
00:03:41,622 --> 00:03:46,060
(Tamura) I had heard that you would change jobs, but starting your own business was unexpected.

65
00:03:46,126 --> 00:03:49,063
(Ryoko) What is "COO"?

66
00:03:49,129 --> 00:03:53,567
(Luna) Chief Operating Officer and Chief Operating Officer.

67
00:03:53,634 --> 00:03:56,570
>> I don't really understand something, but it's amazing!

68
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:59,573
No, no... there are only two people left →

69
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,076
We are also considering expanding overseas.

70
00:04:02,142 --> 00:04:04,578
(Ryoko) Cool! (Luna) It's wonderful.

71
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:08,015
(Bubbly) Would you like some stew?

72
00:04:08,082 --> 00:04:10,517
Oh no, you see, we're about to have a meeting.

73
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:14,021
I just stopped by to say hello today, so I'm going to take it easy.

74
00:04:14,088 --> 00:04:16,590
Well. 📱(Notification sound)

75
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:22,029
(Luna) Night cherry blossom cruise...

76
00:04:22,096 --> 00:04:25,032
>> No, an invitation to a date?

77
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:28,535
Mr. Kitaoji? James? Oh, Ryu-kun?

78
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:32,539
(Ryoko) Huh? who? >> My mom and I have been nice people lately.

79
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:36,043
They're all good-looking and good guys.

80
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:39,046
My recommendation is Ryu.

81
00:04:39,113 --> 00:04:41,048
(Tamura) Hey. (Ryoko) What about your mom?

82
00:04:41,115 --> 00:04:44,051
(Luna) Hmm, everyone is so wonderful.

83
00:04:44,118 --> 00:04:47,054
Everyone has something to offer.

84
00:04:47,121 --> 00:04:49,556
(Ryoko) Huh! Does that mean there is?

85
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:52,059
>> Ah, no, no... there's a difference between what's going on and what's going on.

86
00:04:52,126 --> 00:04:55,062
(Ryoko) Huh? (Tamura) Huh? can be? can be? Thanks...

87
00:04:55,129 --> 00:04:57,564
(Meguru) Welcome. (Masayoshi) Hey!

88
00:04:57,631 --> 00:04:59,566
(Luna) Ma-kun!

89
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:02,569
(Ryoko) Huh? Someone close to you?

90
00:05:02,636 --> 00:05:06,507
(Luna) Ah, Masayoshi Inagaki's maternal cousin.

91
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:08,008
(Masayoshi) Nice to meet you.

92
00:05:08,075 --> 00:05:12,012
(Luna) My friends Ryoko Sawatsuji and Mr. Tamura Kominato →

93
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:14,515
They are friends of Marquee Moon.

94
00:05:14,581 --> 00:05:19,520
>> Hello, I'm Kominato and I'm close friends with Luna!

95
00:05:19,586 --> 00:05:21,522
Hello. (Kominato) Hello, yes.

96
00:05:21,588 --> 00:05:25,526
Well, I have work to do, so good day everyone!

97
00:05:25,592 --> 00:05:27,027
Ah...!

98
00:05:27,094 --> 00:05:29,096
(Luna) Please be careful. >> Thank you.

99
00:05:30,597 --> 00:05:32,533
(Luna) It's rare for me to come to the store.

100
00:05:32,599 --> 00:05:34,535
>> I have something to deliver →

101
00:05:34,601 --> 00:05:38,038
My aunt asked me to give it to you.

102
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:41,041
(Ryoko) Who is your aunt? (Luna) My mother.

103
00:05:41,108 --> 00:05:45,045
>> I don't know the password, so please help me figure it out.

104
00:05:45,112 --> 00:05:47,548
I also want you to check the contents.

105
00:05:47,614 --> 00:05:52,119
(Luna) What do you mean? You didn't ask me to do that...

106
00:05:54,121 --> 00:05:58,559
(Ryoko) This cover says "I am a cat," right?

107
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:01,562
(Luna) Is this his computer?

108
00:06:01,628 --> 00:06:03,063
(Ryoko) That person?

109
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:05,999
>> Apparently, the old man said he wanted it disposed of.

110
00:06:06,066 --> 00:06:09,503
(Luna) Then you should just dispose of it. >> Even if I tell you.

111
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:13,507
Auntie said, I really want you to open it →

112
00:06:13,574 --> 00:06:16,076
It's no good without you.

113
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:24,017
(Tamura) I guess I've been in contact with my cousin.

114
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:28,021
(Ryoko) That computer belongs to mom...

115
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:31,525
(Tamura) I think it's probably my father's.

116
00:06:31,592 --> 00:06:37,030
(Ryoko) Is your mom's house complicated?

117
00:06:37,097 --> 00:06:39,032
(Tamura) Ah...｡

118
00:06:39,099 --> 00:06:41,034
(Ryoko) Ah, sorry, okay.

119
00:06:41,101 --> 00:06:44,605
It's not like I'm going to step in without the person in question.

120
00:06:47,107 --> 00:06:49,543
⟨…However, →

121
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:54,047
When I see mom's face like that, I'm really curious ⟩

122
00:06:54,114 --> 00:06:55,549
>> Huh?

123
00:06:55,616 --> 00:06:58,051
(Drinking sound) (Kikuo) Ah~｡

124
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:03,056
Dr. Shigehara was originally the heir to a large hospital.

125
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:07,995
But I wanted to become a novelist, so I dropped out of medical school without permission.

126
00:07:08,061 --> 00:07:11,498
I ran away from home, angering my father.

127
00:07:11,565 --> 00:07:16,003
I guess he hasn't really returned to his parents' house.

128
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:20,007
(Ryoko) You mean we haven't seen each other for over 10 years?

129
00:07:20,073 --> 00:07:23,510
So what about mom changing her family register?

130
00:07:23,577 --> 00:07:27,514
>> I've confided in my mother, but I'm sure I haven't told my father.

131
00:07:27,581 --> 00:07:31,018
There is already a feud.

132
00:07:31,084 --> 00:07:33,520
I've been keeping my mouth shut even to my mother.

133
00:07:33,587 --> 00:07:36,523
(Ryoko) I see...

134
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:39,026
>> Dr. Shigehara, how are you doing?

135
00:07:39,092 --> 00:07:43,030
I lost the opportunity to contact him due to a change in responsibility.

136
00:07:43,096 --> 00:07:45,532
(Ryoko) Yeah, I'm fine.

137
00:07:45,599 --> 00:07:48,035
>> That would be fine.

138
00:07:48,101 --> 00:07:51,538
Because he's a person with a lot on his plate.

139
00:07:51,605 --> 00:07:54,041
Especially about my father →

140
00:07:54,107 --> 00:07:58,045
For her, it's like life's homework.

141
00:07:58,111 --> 00:08:00,547
(Ryoko) Homework...

142
00:08:00,614 --> 00:08:34,014
♪～

143
00:08:34,081 --> 00:08:36,016
(Eisuke) [Correct]

144
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:49,596
♪～

145
00:08:51,331 --> 00:08:54,701
(Atsushi) Ah, smartphone! I'm coming!

146
00:08:54,768 --> 00:08:56,703
(Ryoko) Yes, please come!

147
00:08:56,770 --> 00:08:59,273
(Kikuo) I'm coming. (Ryoko) Yes, please come.

148
00:09:00,774 --> 00:09:02,709
(sound of door closing)

149
00:09:02,776 --> 00:09:04,711
(Ryoko) Huh? Aroma: Haven't you changed your clothes yet?

150
00:09:04,778 --> 00:09:08,715
I'm going to be late for school. >> I'm going to sleep a little longer from 2nd period today.

151
00:09:08,782 --> 00:09:13,220
Ah, I have a part-time job at night. (Ryoko) Yeah.

152
00:09:13,287 --> 00:09:16,290
(Sound of door closing) 📱(Reception sound)

153
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:20,727
(Luna's voice) "Are you free tonight?"

154
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:31,738
♪～

155
00:09:31,805 --> 00:09:34,241
(Ryoko) Ah! (Luna) Thank you for waiting~｡

156
00:09:34,308 --> 00:09:38,745
(Ryoko) Thank you for the invitation. It's been a while since I went to see the cherry blossoms at night.

157
00:09:38,812 --> 00:09:40,247
(Luna) Ah.

158
00:09:40,314 --> 00:09:43,250
(Ryoko) Eh, Tamura-san too? (Tamura) Hello.

159
00:09:43,317 --> 00:09:45,752
(Luna) Since she said she was on vacation, I invited her along.

160
00:09:45,819 --> 00:09:48,255
It looked like I had free time. (Tamura) No, I don't have free time.

161
00:09:48,322 --> 00:09:51,258
It's just that the training has just started and I haven't been to the field yet...

162
00:09:51,325 --> 00:09:54,328
(Luna) Yes, yes, let's go. (Ryoko) Aha...｡

163
00:09:57,831 --> 00:10:00,267
(Tamura) So why Shimokitazawa?

164
00:10:00,334 --> 00:10:02,269
(Luna) Is there a place I want to visit?

165
00:10:02,336 --> 00:10:05,272
I'm thinking of trying to analyze my computer's password.

166
00:10:05,339 --> 00:10:06,773
(Ryoko) Huh?

167
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:10,777
(Luna) It's my mother's request, and I owe her many things.

168
00:10:10,844 --> 00:10:12,779
(Ryoko) I see.

169
00:10:12,846 --> 00:10:15,782
(Luna) Judging from the personality of the computer owner →

170
00:10:15,849 --> 00:10:19,786
The password is probably related to "I am a cat."

171
00:10:19,853 --> 00:10:22,289
(Luna's voice) That background image is from the first edition →

172
00:10:22,356 --> 00:10:25,292
First of all, I'm thinking of getting a reprint of the first edition →

173
00:10:25,359 --> 00:10:28,295
I got it on hold at a used bookstore in Shimokita.

174
00:10:28,362 --> 00:10:31,798
(Ryoko) Hey, I hope you know the password.

175
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:34,301
(Luna) Maybe the owner of the used bookstore can help.

176
00:10:34,368 --> 00:10:36,303
My name is Kurata-san →

177
00:10:36,370 --> 00:10:39,306
We used to work together in a mystery-solving club a long time ago.

178
00:10:39,373 --> 00:10:41,308
(Tamura) Mystery solving circle?

179
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:44,811
>> [Time up! ]

180
00:10:44,878 --> 00:10:46,880
[The correct answer is...]

181
00:10:49,383 --> 00:10:53,253
[It's Nomiya-san again! ] [Applause]

182
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:58,258
(Kurata) [Great job! Solving mysteries with literary knowledge]

183
00:10:58,325 --> 00:11:01,762
[Wow, that's great! ] (Luna) [Excuse me]

184
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:05,265
(Ryoko) Hey, it's nice to have common interests.

185
00:11:05,332 --> 00:11:08,835
(Luna) It's been six years since we met.

186
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:13,774
(Sound of phone button being pressed)

187
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,776
(sound of door opening)

188
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:17,844
(noise)

189
00:11:22,349 --> 00:11:24,284
(Tamura) Oh, that's amazing.

190
00:11:24,351 --> 00:11:28,789
(Ryoko) Unlike cherry blossoms under the sun, cherry blossoms at night are more impressive.

191
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:31,792
I'd say it's a bit chilling.

192
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:34,795
(Tamura) There are dead bodies buried under the cherry blossom trees.

193
00:11:34,861 --> 00:11:37,798
(Ryoko) What!? (Tamura) I thought there was a novel like that.

194
00:11:37,864 --> 00:11:41,802
(Ryoko) Huh... It feels strangely realistic and scary when the detective says that.

195
00:11:41,868 --> 00:11:43,804
(Tamura) Huh? Is it Ango Sakaguchi?

196
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,806
(Luna) There are many people who think so →

197
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:48,308
Actually, Mr. Motojiro Kajii.

198
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:50,310
(Tamura) Ah, you're from Lemon.

199
00:11:50,377 --> 00:11:53,246
(Luna) Yes, "under the cherry tree."

200
00:11:53,313 --> 00:11:56,249
Feelings of awe at things that are too beautiful →

201
00:11:56,316 --> 00:11:58,752
A short story with bold expressions.

202
00:11:58,819 --> 00:12:00,754
(Ryoko) Hey.

203
00:12:00,821 --> 00:12:05,759
(Luna) Ango Sakaguchi wrote ``Under the Cherry Blossom Forest in Full Bloom.''

204
00:12:05,826 --> 00:12:08,762
(Ryoko) Both are under the tree.

205
00:12:08,829 --> 00:12:12,265
What kind of story is that? (Luna) Good to hear from you.

206
00:12:12,332 --> 00:12:17,771
This is a story about a bandit who similarly finds cherry blossoms terrifying.

207
00:12:17,838 --> 00:12:20,774
The beautiful woman that the bandit married →

208
00:12:20,841 --> 00:12:24,277
I had a hobby of playing with severed human heads.

209
00:12:24,344 --> 00:12:28,782
The bandits continued to hunt people's heads as ordered by her, but →

210
00:12:28,849 --> 00:12:32,285
Eventually, he grew tired of continuing this cruel deed.

211
00:12:32,352 --> 00:12:35,789
He carries the woman on his back and returns to the mountain where he used to live.

212
00:12:35,856 --> 00:12:38,291
It was the time when the cherry blossoms were in full bloom.

213
00:12:38,358 --> 00:12:42,796
The bandit passes under the cherry tree, feeling fearful.

214
00:12:42,863 --> 00:12:47,300
When I looked back, my beautiful wife had turned into an ugly demon →

215
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:49,302
He strangles the bandits.

216
00:12:49,369 --> 00:12:52,305
When the bandit panicked and strangled the demon, →

217
00:12:52,372 --> 00:12:56,743
Before she knew it, the demon returned to her female form and took her last breath.

218
00:12:56,810 --> 00:13:01,248
When a bandit tries to touch a woman under the falling cherry blossoms→

219
00:13:01,314 --> 00:13:03,750
The woman becomes a cherry blossom petal →

220
00:13:03,817 --> 00:13:07,254
It would disappear.

221
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:11,258
(Ryoko) In the end, it turns into cherry blossom petals and disappears →

222
00:13:11,324 --> 00:13:13,260
It's scary but beautiful.

223
00:13:13,326 --> 00:13:15,762
(Luna) Yes, it's scary but beautiful.

224
00:13:15,829 --> 00:13:18,765
A story like the cherry blossoms themselves.

225
00:13:18,832 --> 00:13:22,769
Mr. Sakaguchi is an all-around writer who is not only good at pure literature →

226
00:13:22,836 --> 00:13:26,273
Historical novels like ``Oda Nobunaga'' are also highly rated.

227
00:13:26,339 --> 00:13:29,276
I also work on translations of French literature.

228
00:13:29,342 --> 00:13:31,778
Criticisms such as ``the theory of depravity'' are also famous.

229
00:13:31,845 --> 00:13:34,281
Genius to say the least.

230
00:13:34,347 --> 00:13:37,284
(Tamura) Wow, I learned a lot. (Ryoko) Hey!

231
00:13:37,350 --> 00:13:41,288
Lately, thanks to my mom, I've started to wake up to literature.

232
00:13:41,354 --> 00:13:44,357
Well, I don't know if it's difficult.

233
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:49,863
(Luna) Ah, there it is, Sakura Shobo.

234
00:13:52,365 --> 00:13:54,801
Please excuse me.

235
00:13:56,803 --> 00:13:59,239
Ha, Kurata-san!

236
00:13:59,306 --> 00:14:01,241
(Ryoko) Ah! (Tamura) What!?

237
00:14:01,308 --> 00:14:05,245
(Luna) Mr. Kurata! Can you hear me?

238
00:14:05,312 --> 00:14:07,247
Mr. Tamura. (Tamura) Ah.

239
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:11,251
(Luna: Tamura) Se-no. (Luna) Give me your arm.

240
00:14:11,318 --> 00:14:14,754
(Operation sound) 📱 (Ring sound)

241
00:14:14,821 --> 00:14:17,757
📱 Call 119. Is there a fire? Is it an emergency?

242
00:14:17,824 --> 00:14:22,262
(Luna) It's an emergency! An elderly man collapses, bleeding from the head.

243
00:14:22,329 --> 00:14:23,763
I'm unconscious.

244
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:26,833
(Tamura) It wasn't an accident. I'll contact the police.

245
00:14:29,836 --> 00:14:31,771
(Emergency personnel) Ichi ni san.

246
00:14:31,838 --> 00:14:33,273
(Paramedics) Hurry up the transport.

247
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:36,276
(Paramedic) Can someone please give me a ride? (Tamura) I'll go.

248
00:14:36,343 --> 00:14:39,779
The detectives from Yozawa Police Station are coming, so the two of you should talk about the circumstances when you found them.

249
00:14:39,846 --> 00:14:41,348
(Luna) I understand.

250
00:14:42,849 --> 00:14:44,784
(camera shutter sound)

251
00:14:44,851 --> 00:14:47,787
(Yano) Could you please help me collect fingerprints?

252
00:14:47,854 --> 00:14:50,290
We have to exclude the fingerprints of both of you.

253
00:14:50,357 --> 00:14:54,227
I would also like to take a look at your bag.

254
00:14:54,294 --> 00:14:56,229
(Ryoko) Are we being suspected?

255
00:14:56,296 --> 00:14:59,232
(Luna) It can't be helped to doubt the first discoverer.

256
00:14:59,299 --> 00:15:02,736
When I was in Osaka, Mr. Tamura guaranteed my identity...

257
00:15:02,802 --> 00:15:05,238
Ah, I see.

258
00:15:05,305 --> 00:15:07,741
>> Replaced! (Ambulance worker) Fumihiko Kurata, 77 years old.

259
00:15:07,807 --> 00:15:10,744
He was found lying on the ground bleeding from the head.

260
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:12,812
Please wait here.

261
00:15:17,317 --> 00:15:19,319
(Yano) Excuse me.

262
00:15:21,321 --> 00:15:24,257
We spoke to Detective Tamura.

263
00:15:24,324 --> 00:15:27,761
It seems that he cooperated with several cases in Osaka.

264
00:15:27,827 --> 00:15:29,262
(Ryoko) That's right.

265
00:15:29,329 --> 00:15:32,265
>>I didn't really understand what literature meant.

266
00:15:32,332 --> 00:15:34,768
(Ryoko) Is this a story about solving a case through literature?

267
00:15:34,834 --> 00:15:37,270
>> That's what you said →

268
00:15:37,337 --> 00:15:41,775
Investigation is different from play.

269
00:15:41,841 --> 00:15:44,277
I'm glad you're back now.

270
00:15:44,344 --> 00:15:47,280
After this, there will be an in-store inspection.

271
00:15:47,347 --> 00:15:50,784
(Luna) Ryunosuke Akutagawa's "Hell Change" from Noda Shobo.

272
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:53,720
Egawa version of Yasunari Kawabata's ``Dancer of Izu''.

273
00:15:53,787 --> 00:15:56,723
Takemura Shobo Ango Sakaguchi's "Kurotani Village".

274
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:59,793
>> Yes? (Luna) This is a stolen book.

275
00:16:01,795 --> 00:16:03,730
>> How do you know?

276
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:08,234
(Luna) Some stores store expensive books in a locked show case.

277
00:16:08,301 --> 00:16:10,236
It is difficult to shoplift at this store →

278
00:16:10,303 --> 00:16:12,739
It looks like it's on the top of your bookshelf.

279
00:16:12,806 --> 00:16:15,241
Books are arranged by author →

280
00:16:15,308 --> 00:16:19,746
There are unnatural gaps in each row.

281
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:21,748
(Ryoko) Oh, that's true.

282
00:16:21,815 --> 00:16:25,752
(Luna) The "Hell Change", "Dancer of Izu", and "Kurotani Village" that I mentioned earlier are →

283
00:16:25,819 --> 00:16:29,255
It is known among enthusiasts as an especially expensive old book.

284
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:32,258
It's probably in the millions.

285
00:16:32,325 --> 00:16:34,761
>> Mr. Miyashita. (Miyashita) Yes.

286
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:37,764
At your local used bookstore or online flea market →

287
00:16:37,831 --> 00:16:40,266
Please check if there are any items for sale.

288
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,268
Is your cash stolen?

289
00:16:42,335 --> 00:16:44,771
(Miyashita) All the cash has been taken out.

290
00:16:44,838 --> 00:16:46,773
It's definitely a thief.

291
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:50,777
(Luna) Hmm, how about that? (Ryoko) Huh? No?

292
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:54,714
(Luna) If you stole those three books, you're probably an old book buff.

293
00:16:54,781 --> 00:16:56,716
But mania is like this→

294
00:16:56,783 --> 00:16:59,786
I feel like I won't scatter the books.

295
00:17:02,789 --> 00:17:06,726
(Luna) 10 yen? Why only one on the tray?

296
00:17:06,793 --> 00:17:09,229
(Ryoko) Did someone forget their change?

297
00:17:09,295 --> 00:17:14,234
>> Huh, robbers won't take your coins.

298
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:18,738
Ah! Please don't touch it! Forensics are still investigating.

299
00:17:18,805 --> 00:17:37,323
♪～

300
00:17:39,993 --> 00:17:43,430
(buzz)

301
00:17:43,496 --> 00:17:46,933
(Suzumoto) Excuse me. Excuse me. Did something happen to that Mr. Kurata?

302
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,436
(Yano's voice) Mr. Suzumoto from Smart Transport.

303
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:51,938
Do you know Mr. Kurata?

304
00:17:52,005 --> 00:17:56,443
Yes, we just make small talk during delivery.

305
00:17:56,509 --> 00:17:58,445
He always brings me drinks →

306
00:17:58,511 --> 00:18:00,447
I'm being treated well.

307
00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:02,449
Kurata-san, are you okay?

308
00:18:02,515 --> 00:18:05,952
He survived, but is currently undergoing emergency surgery.

309
00:18:06,019 --> 00:18:08,455
I had just delivered it.

310
00:18:08,521 --> 00:18:11,958
I was glad that Sakura-san came today.

311
00:18:12,025 --> 00:18:15,962
cherry blossoms? >>Oh, it's your grandchild.

312
00:18:16,029 --> 00:18:18,465
(Suzumoto's voice) I was just leaving when I came to make the delivery.

313
00:18:18,531 --> 00:18:20,967
[Hello, this is Smart Transport] (Kurata) [Thank you for your hard work]

314
00:18:21,034 --> 00:18:23,470
(Suzumoto) [Excuse me] (Yano's voice) What are your grandchild's characteristics?

315
00:18:23,536 --> 00:18:25,472
Age, height, whatever.

316
00:18:25,538 --> 00:18:28,475
I'm probably around twenty years old.

317
00:18:28,541 --> 00:18:32,979
She was petite and delicate, and was wearing a pale pink dress.

318
00:18:33,046 --> 00:18:34,981
Ah, that's right.

319
00:18:35,048 --> 00:18:36,549
Sorry.

320
00:18:38,051 --> 00:18:40,487
This baby is Sakura.

321
00:18:40,553 --> 00:18:43,490
She often told me stories about her daughter's family.

322
00:18:43,556 --> 00:18:45,492
Because Kurata-san likes cherry blossoms →

323
00:18:45,558 --> 00:18:47,994
She also named her grandchild "Sakura."

324
00:18:48,061 --> 00:18:50,497
(Ryoko) Wow, so cute.

325
00:18:50,563 --> 00:18:53,500
Probably about the same as my daughter now.

326
00:18:53,566 --> 00:18:55,935
>> Don't touch it!

327
00:18:56,002 --> 00:18:57,937
(Ryoko) Sorry...

328
00:18:58,004 --> 00:19:01,441
(Yano) Around what time did you see your grandchild Sakura?

329
00:19:01,508 --> 00:19:03,443
About 30 minutes ago.

330
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:06,446
(Suzumoto's voice) When I brought the book home, I ran into a different person.

331
00:19:06,513 --> 00:19:11,451
But something strange happened.

332
00:19:11,518 --> 00:19:13,453
After receiving the stamp →

333
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:15,955
I was heading to the next delivery destination on my bicycle.

334
00:19:16,022 --> 00:19:18,458
It just ended up being a chase after Sakura-san.

335
00:19:18,525 --> 00:19:21,461
And she turned the corner.

336
00:19:21,528 --> 00:19:23,963
Me too, as soon as I turned the corner →

337
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:27,967
I can't find her anywhere.

338
00:19:28,034 --> 00:19:30,470
It suddenly disappeared.

339
00:19:30,537 --> 00:19:32,972
(Luna) Disappeared? (Suzumoto) Yes.

340
00:19:33,039 --> 00:19:35,975
And even though there was no wind, it turned just around the corner →

341
00:19:36,042 --> 00:19:37,977
The cherry blossoms are dancing fluffy →

342
00:19:38,044 --> 00:19:41,981
It seems like it disappeared along with the cherry blossoms.

343
00:19:42,048 --> 00:19:46,986
I feel like I've been pinched by a fox.

344
00:19:47,053 --> 00:19:53,493
(Ryoko) It disappears with the cherry blossoms... It's like the world of Ango Sakaguchi.

345
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:55,428
>> Grandchild Sakura and her parents →

346
00:19:55,495 --> 00:19:58,431
Apparently he died in a traffic accident 18 years ago.

347
00:19:58,498 --> 00:20:01,434
(All) Huh? >> No, that can't be true!

348
00:20:01,501 --> 00:20:04,437
Because Mr. Kurata clearly told me that it was his grandson, Sakura.

349
00:20:04,504 --> 00:20:08,942
And I didn't even hear a word about my daughter's family being dead...

350
00:20:09,008 --> 00:20:11,444
(Ryoko) Ghost...

351
00:20:11,511 --> 00:20:15,448
>> What!? >> That can't be true.

352
00:20:15,515 --> 00:20:19,953
There are two possibilities based on your eyewitness testimony.

353
00:20:20,019 --> 00:20:23,456
One is that someone pretended to be Sakura.

354
00:20:23,523 --> 00:20:27,460
However, in this case, Mr. Kurata would not believe it, so it would not hold true.

355
00:20:27,527 --> 00:20:30,964
The other one is →

356
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:35,468
The eyewitness testimony itself was false. (Ryoko) What?

357
00:20:35,535 --> 00:20:37,971
So does that mean he's lying?

358
00:20:38,037 --> 00:20:39,973
>> No, no...! Is there any point in lying like that?

359
00:20:40,039 --> 00:20:43,476
(Yano) It is also possible that this was done to confuse the investigation.

360
00:20:43,543 --> 00:20:45,478
The crime of robbery that I committed →

361
00:20:45,545 --> 00:20:49,482
They're trying to impersonate a fictional character who doesn't exist.

362
00:20:49,549 --> 00:20:52,485
(Luna) That's not true. >> Yes?

363
00:20:52,552 --> 00:20:55,421
(Luna) If you tell me about the sightings of Sakura-san disappearing →

364
00:20:55,488 --> 00:20:57,423
I feel even more suspicious →

365
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:59,926
I won't be coming back here in the first place.

366
00:20:59,993 --> 00:21:03,930
>> That's right, that's right! (Ryoko) Certainly.

367
00:21:03,997 --> 00:21:07,500
>> If so, who the hell is that woman?

368
00:21:09,502 --> 00:21:12,939
Excuse me while I'm talking, this is what I found under the bookshelf.

369
00:21:13,006 --> 00:21:15,008
(Yano) What about fingerprints? (Miyashita) I took it.

370
00:21:18,011 --> 00:21:21,514
(Yano) This is the book that Mr. Nomiya said he ordered over the phone.

371
00:21:23,516 --> 00:21:28,021
(Luna) All I ordered was ``I am a cat.''

372
00:21:31,524 --> 00:21:33,960
(Yano) Huh?

373
00:21:34,027 --> 00:21:36,963
Let's send it for forensic examination. (Miyashita) Yes.

374
00:21:37,030 --> 00:21:45,972
♪～

375
00:21:46,039 --> 00:21:47,473
📱(Camera shutter sound)

376
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:49,542
📱(vibration sound)

377
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:57,417
(Tamura) What? this.

378
00:21:57,483 --> 00:22:00,486
(Luna's voice) "Mr. Tamura, there's something I want you to look into."

379
00:22:05,124 --> 00:22:07,627
>> Please don't touch it!

380
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:16,502
yeah?

381
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:23,443
I see. Is that so?

382
00:22:23,509 --> 00:22:28,448
The victim, Mr. Kurata, appears to have had a decline in cognitive function.

383
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:29,949
(Ryoko) Huh?

384
00:22:30,016 --> 00:22:31,884
>> Even though I have a brand new water purifier →

385
00:22:31,951 --> 00:22:34,887
I have a contract for a water server.

386
00:22:34,954 --> 00:22:37,390
My grandfather also had dementia.

387
00:22:37,457 --> 00:22:40,393
I had a habit of buying the same thing over and over again.

388
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:44,397
It was probably taken advantage of by multiple companies.

389
00:22:44,464 --> 00:22:48,901
(Luna) Different companies are involved in the renovation of the store.

390
00:22:48,968 --> 00:22:50,403
>> What!?

391
00:22:50,470 --> 00:22:53,406
(Luna) The wall and door colors don't match.

392
00:22:53,473 --> 00:22:57,410
Many lights are installed in places where they are not needed.

393
00:22:57,477 --> 00:23:01,914
Mr. Kurata had signed contracts as told by multiple companies.

394
00:23:01,981 --> 00:23:04,917
(Ryoko) For the elderly whose judgment has deteriorated →

395
00:23:04,984 --> 00:23:08,421
Unscrupulous dealers selling all kinds of things?

396
00:23:08,488 --> 00:23:09,922
>> Please wait.

397
00:23:09,989 --> 00:23:11,924
I often stood and talked with Mr. Kurata→

398
00:23:11,991 --> 00:23:13,926
It didn't look like that at all.

399
00:23:13,993 --> 00:23:15,928
From smartphone apps to the latest tablets →

400
00:23:15,995 --> 00:23:17,930
I used it well.

401
00:23:17,997 --> 00:23:21,434
There are many people who seem solid at first glance.

402
00:23:21,501 --> 00:23:26,439
All of this could be explained if cognitive function had declined.

403
00:23:26,506 --> 00:23:28,941
I was also preparing books that I didn't order.

404
00:23:29,008 --> 00:23:31,377
Forget that Sakura-san passed away →

405
00:23:31,444 --> 00:23:35,882
That's probably why he thought others were his grandchildren.

406
00:23:35,948 --> 00:23:38,885
So who was it? That girl.

407
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:42,955
(Ryoko) I guess she thought the customer was her grandchild.

408
00:23:46,459 --> 00:23:48,394
>>Special fraud.

409
00:23:48,461 --> 00:23:51,898
(Ryoko) Special fraud means me-or-me fraud, right?

410
00:23:51,964 --> 00:23:54,901
>> It's been happening a lot around here lately.

411
00:23:54,967 --> 00:23:56,903
In the first place →

412
00:23:56,969 --> 00:24:00,907
It's unnatural for young women to come and buy books that cost millions.

413
00:24:00,973 --> 00:24:05,912
They come in contact with elderly people whose judgment has deteriorated, pretending to be their relatives.

414
00:24:05,978 --> 00:24:08,915
However, the person who actually comes to receive the money is →

415
00:24:08,981 --> 00:24:11,417
Often it's another person.

416
00:24:11,484 --> 00:24:14,921
(Luna) He's a person called a receiver. >> That's right.

417
00:24:14,987 --> 00:24:18,424
If you look at his face, you'll know it's not him.

418
00:24:18,491 --> 00:24:21,427
However, this time, from the phone call I made beforehand →

419
00:24:21,494 --> 00:24:23,930
It turns out that Mr. Kurata's cognitive function is declining →

420
00:24:23,996 --> 00:24:27,433
I thought it would be more effective if I went as my grandson himself.

421
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:31,871
(Luna) If it's a special scam, the mystery of the woman's disappearance can be solved.

422
00:24:31,938 --> 00:24:33,873
>> Huh? What do you mean?

423
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:36,876
(Luna) Special fraud is carried out in groups.

424
00:24:36,943 --> 00:24:40,379
Make calls in addition to the receiver → Caller →

425
00:24:40,446 --> 00:24:43,382
Watchman and in some cases →

426
00:24:43,449 --> 00:24:46,385
I heard that there is also a person in charge of picking up and dropping off children.

427
00:24:46,452 --> 00:24:48,387
>> I see.

428
00:24:48,454 --> 00:24:52,391
There was a shuttle waiting around the corner.

429
00:24:52,458 --> 00:24:57,964
(Luna) As soon as she got in, the courtesy car drove away at great speed.

430
00:25:04,971 --> 00:25:08,908
(Ryoko) If so, who caused Kurata-san's injury?

431
00:25:08,975 --> 00:25:12,411
After the female receiver and him left the store →

432
00:25:12,478 --> 00:25:14,914
Does that mean someone hit you?

433
00:25:14,981 --> 00:25:18,417
At about the same time on the same day →

434
00:25:18,484 --> 00:25:20,920
Ore Ore scam and attack incident →

435
00:25:20,987 --> 00:25:23,923
Do things happen one after the other?

436
00:25:23,990 --> 00:25:29,929
📱(vibration sound)

437
00:25:29,996 --> 00:25:31,931
(Luna) Hello, Mr. Tamura.

438
00:25:31,998 --> 00:25:34,500
(Tamura) I was able to contact the sales representatives.

439
00:25:36,002 --> 00:25:38,004
(Luna) Thank you.

440
00:25:40,006 --> 00:25:44,443
A new fact has been discovered regarding Mr. Kurata's cognitive function.

441
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,946
Detective Tamura investigated.

442
00:25:47,013 --> 00:25:48,447
>> Yes?

443
00:25:48,514 --> 00:25:51,450
(Luna) According to the person in charge of the water server →

444
00:25:51,517 --> 00:25:55,955
When I went into sales, I was told they already had a water purifier.→

445
00:25:56,022 --> 00:26:00,459
Mr. Kurata generously agreed to the contract.

446
00:26:00,526 --> 00:26:05,464
Among the sales people in charge of this area, Sakura Shobo is bought without any refusal →

447
00:26:05,531 --> 00:26:07,967
It is said to be known for...

448
00:26:08,034 --> 00:26:10,970
(Luna's voice) Because I don't have a family to leave behind a legacy →

449
00:26:11,037 --> 00:26:13,472
Buy from people who are having trouble meeting sales quotas →

450
00:26:13,539 --> 00:26:15,975
He said he was helping people.

451
00:26:16,042 --> 00:26:18,978
The same goes for remodelers.

452
00:26:19,045 --> 00:26:21,480
(Ryoko) It's not that my cognitive function has declined →

453
00:26:21,547 --> 00:26:23,983
Does that mean he was a kind person?

454
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:27,987
>> That's right! Mr. Kurata is really a nice person.

455
00:26:28,054 --> 00:26:30,923
(Ryoko) In that case, Mr. Kurata →

456
00:26:30,990 --> 00:26:34,427
When I received a phone call that my grandson was in trouble →

457
00:26:34,493 --> 00:26:37,430
Of course you knew it was a scam, right?

458
00:26:37,496 --> 00:26:40,933
☏(Female) [Moshi Moshi Grandpa Me]

459
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:44,437
(Ryoko's voice) But why didn't you report it right away?

460
00:26:44,503 --> 00:26:48,441
Moreover, Mr. Kurata, you gave the book to that woman, right?

461
00:26:48,507 --> 00:26:50,509
Isn't it weird?

462
00:26:52,511 --> 00:26:57,516
(Luna) There should be hints to uncovering the incident hidden in those three books.

463
00:27:06,659 --> 00:27:10,096
(Luna) There's blood on both the bag and the book →

464
00:27:10,096 --> 00:27:12,031
After Mr. Kurata was attacked →

465
00:27:12,098 --> 00:27:16,035
This means that you have added these three books to your bag.

466
00:27:16,102 --> 00:27:18,471
Moreover, in this complete collection →

467
00:27:18,537 --> 00:27:20,539
It has creases.

468
00:27:28,547 --> 00:27:31,484
(Ryoko) ``Record of a small goat.''

469
00:27:31,550 --> 00:27:33,986
(Luna) Probably using these three works→

470
00:27:34,053 --> 00:27:37,490
Mr. Kurata tried to tell me something.

471
00:27:37,556 --> 00:27:39,492
(Ryoko) So "Angou"?

472
00:27:39,558 --> 00:27:41,994
>> No, no, it's a code →

473
00:27:42,061 --> 00:27:44,997
Can a normal person come up with it right away?

474
00:27:45,064 --> 00:27:48,501
And even though he was seriously injured.

475
00:27:48,567 --> 00:27:52,505
(Luna) Mr. Kurata is a mystery maniac who also belongs to a mystery solving club.

476
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:55,007
>> Don't do such drowsy things →

477
00:27:55,074 --> 00:27:57,510
Isn't it okay to leave a note?

478
00:27:57,576 --> 00:28:00,513
(Luna) If it's a memo, the criminal will find it and hide it.

479
00:28:00,579 --> 00:28:02,014
>> I see!

480
00:28:02,081 --> 00:28:05,017
Suppose that theory is correct→

481
00:28:05,084 --> 00:28:08,521
Who the hell attacked Mr. Kurata?

482
00:28:08,587 --> 00:28:13,526
(Luna) The culprit is a lookout for a special fraud group.

483
00:28:13,592 --> 00:28:17,463
(Ryoko) Does that mean she's a friend of the woman who was pretending to be Sakura?

484
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:18,964
(Luna) Yes.

485
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:22,968
If I were to write a novel based on this incident →

486
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:25,971
It will unfold like this.

487
00:28:26,038 --> 00:28:28,974
I was watching over Mr. Kurata outside the store →

488
00:28:29,041 --> 00:28:31,977
After Ukeko and Suzumoto-san leave the store →

489
00:28:32,044 --> 00:28:34,480
Mr. Kurata, who was aware of the fraud, →

490
00:28:34,547 --> 00:28:37,983
They attacked me when I was trying to report it.

491
00:28:38,050 --> 00:28:40,986
>> Ah! Come to think of it, when I go home →

492
00:28:41,053 --> 00:28:44,490
Mr. Kurata: I was trying to call someone.

493
00:28:44,557 --> 00:28:47,493
(Luna's voice) Mr. Kurata was attacked by the guard →

494
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:51,564
The recoil hit the bookshelf and fell to the floor.

495
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:56,001
The watcher stole cash from the cash register.

496
00:28:56,068 --> 00:28:58,504
Although Mr. Kurata was in a daze, →

497
00:28:58,571 --> 00:29:00,506
Don't let the criminal notice →

498
00:29:00,573 --> 00:29:04,577
I tried to leave clues with the books scattered in front of me.

499
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:10,082
(Ryoko) Is it a code that leads to the culprit...?

500
00:29:11,584 --> 00:29:15,521
>> I see. Isn't it easy?

501
00:29:15,588 --> 00:29:17,957
It's the criminal's name.

502
00:29:18,023 --> 00:29:21,961
The author of all three books is Ango Sakaguchi.

503
00:29:22,027 --> 00:29:25,965
In other words, I was defeated by a man named Sakaguchi.

504
00:29:26,031 --> 00:29:28,968
(Ryoko: Suzumoto) Ah~｡

505
00:29:29,034 --> 00:29:32,972
(Luna) Unfortunately, I think that theory is wrong.

506
00:29:33,038 --> 00:29:34,473
>> Huh?

507
00:29:34,540 --> 00:29:37,476
(Luna) If the culprit finds these three books →

508
00:29:37,543 --> 00:29:40,980
If it is a code that conveys your name, it will be discovered immediately.

509
00:29:41,046 --> 00:29:43,983
And “Record of a small goat” →

510
00:29:44,049 --> 00:29:46,485
There is no explanation for the creases.

511
00:29:46,552 --> 00:29:48,487
(Ryoko: Suzumoto) Indeed.

512
00:29:48,554 --> 00:29:51,490
So what do you mean?

513
00:29:51,557 --> 00:29:54,493
(Luna) I'm about to decipher that.

514
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:57,062
>> Is there a hint in the title?

515
00:29:59,565 --> 00:30:06,005
(Ryoko) “Night” “Princess” “Ears” “Man” →

516
00:30:06,071 --> 00:30:08,507
"goat".

517
00:30:08,574 --> 00:30:11,510
(Suzumoto) The culprit is...

518
00:30:11,577 --> 00:30:13,512
goat.

519
00:30:13,579 --> 00:30:15,514
There's no way.

520
00:30:15,581 --> 00:30:19,451
(Ryoko) Do your ears have any characteristics? Do you have big ears?

521
00:30:19,518 --> 00:30:25,024
>> Huh, it's that simple hahaha...｡

522
00:30:30,529 --> 00:30:36,468
♪～

523
00:30:36,535 --> 00:30:38,971
What are you doing? (Luna: Ryoko) Shh!

524
00:30:39,038 --> 00:30:48,981
♪～

525
00:30:49,048 --> 00:30:50,482
(Luna) 《Ears...》

526
00:30:50,549 --> 00:30:52,484
(Ryoko) [Her ears are big]

527
00:30:52,551 --> 00:30:54,486
(Luna) 《The book I handed you...》

528
00:30:54,553 --> 00:30:57,489
(Yano) [Young women come to buy books that cost millions →

529
00:30:57,556 --> 00:30:59,992
It's unnatural]

530
00:31:00,059 --> 00:31:01,994
(Luna) 《Code...》

531
00:31:02,061 --> 00:31:05,497
>> [Solving mysteries with literary knowledge]

532
00:31:05,564 --> 00:31:06,999
(Luna) 《App…》

533
00:31:07,066 --> 00:31:11,003
(Suzumoto) [He even used the latest tablet]

534
00:31:11,070 --> 00:31:14,006
(Luna) 《The car disappeared with the cherry blossoms...》

535
00:31:14,073 --> 00:31:17,509
(Suzumoto) [Not a single word about my daughter's family being dead...]

536
00:31:21,013 --> 00:31:23,015
(Luna) We are connected.

537
00:31:27,519 --> 00:31:29,521
(Tamura) Understood.

538
00:31:45,537 --> 00:31:47,539
(Tamura) There it was.

539
00:31:54,046 --> 00:31:56,048
(Tamura) It's bingo.

540
00:31:58,050 --> 00:32:00,552
(Luna) This is Detective Tamura.

541
00:32:02,554 --> 00:32:06,492
>> Yes, this is Yano from Daizawa Police Station.

542
00:32:06,558 --> 00:32:08,994
Huh?

543
00:32:09,061 --> 00:32:12,064
Understood, I'll be heading over right away.

544
00:32:13,565 --> 00:32:17,936
Mr. Nomiya, thank you for your cooperation.

545
00:32:18,003 --> 00:32:20,506
Let's go. Yes.

546
00:32:24,009 --> 00:32:25,944
(Ryoko) What? What do you mean?

547
00:32:26,011 --> 00:32:28,948
(Luna) As Ryoko said, the hint is in your ears.

548
00:32:29,014 --> 00:32:32,451
However, this code is not the culprit →

549
00:32:32,518 --> 00:32:34,953
It was about Mr. Kurata himself.

550
00:32:35,020 --> 00:32:39,458
There was a time when Mr. Ango Sakaguchi had difficulty hearing →

551
00:32:39,525 --> 00:32:42,961
I wrote about this in ``Records of a Little Goat.''

552
00:32:43,028 --> 00:32:45,964
Mr. Kurata used the teacher's book →

553
00:32:46,031 --> 00:32:50,469
He tried to tell me that his hearing was bad.

554
00:32:50,536 --> 00:32:52,471
What Mr. Kurata used was →

555
00:32:52,538 --> 00:32:55,474
Hearing aids that can be linked with smartphones →

556
00:32:55,541 --> 00:32:58,477
Even if you lose it, you can search for it.

557
00:32:58,544 --> 00:33:02,981
Before I could report it to the police, my child arrived.

558
00:33:03,048 --> 00:33:04,483
>> [Nice to see you here]

559
00:33:04,550 --> 00:33:06,986
(Luna) Mr. Kurata hands the book to the child →

560
00:33:07,052 --> 00:33:09,988
I put a hearing aid in the bag.

561
00:33:10,055 --> 00:33:14,993
If we track them, we can uncover the base of the special fraudster.

562
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:17,996
Please report it again after the child returns →

563
00:33:18,063 --> 00:33:20,499
I'm planning to have my hearing aids tracked →

564
00:33:20,566 --> 00:33:24,002
I encountered an unexpected attack.

565
00:33:24,069 --> 00:33:27,506
I feel like I need to tell someone that I got a hearing aid →

566
00:33:27,573 --> 00:33:32,578
He put three books in a paper bag as a code for me.

567
00:33:36,081 --> 00:33:38,083
(Tamura) It's the police!

568
00:33:39,585 --> 00:33:46,025
(commotion)

569
00:33:46,091 --> 00:33:47,526
\Let go! /

570
00:33:47,593 --> 00:33:57,536
♪～

571
00:33:57,603 --> 00:33:59,538
(Ryoko) The girl who receives the child is →

572
00:33:59,605 --> 00:34:02,541
Why did he resort to fraud?

573
00:34:02,608 --> 00:34:08,046
I have a child around the same age, so it's not just people.

574
00:34:08,113 --> 00:34:12,551
(Luna) Professor Ango Sakaguchi says this in ``The Theory of Depravity.''

575
00:34:12,618 --> 00:34:16,555
"People live and people fall."

576
00:34:16,622 --> 00:34:19,992
(Ryoko) I want to stop it if I can.

577
00:34:20,058 --> 00:34:23,996
I don't want my family or loved ones to fall.

578
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:26,064
(Luna) Looks like Ryoko.

579
00:34:28,067 --> 00:34:34,006
(Ryoko) The bandit couple in “Under the Cherry Blossom Forest in Full Bloom” are also corrupt people, right?

580
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:37,509
But the bandits should stop abusing people →

581
00:34:37,576 --> 00:34:39,511
I tried to go back to the mountain.

582
00:34:39,578 --> 00:34:43,515
It's also about the wife who wants his head →

583
00:34:43,582 --> 00:34:47,519
I wonder if he was trying to save me from corruption.

584
00:34:47,586 --> 00:34:50,022
(Luna) Save me from corruption...

585
00:34:50,088 --> 00:35:00,532
♪～

586
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:06,104
(Luna) Haha, I understand the mystery of the 10 yen coin.

587
00:35:11,176 --> 00:35:15,113
(Luna) I was relieved to have regained consciousness.

588
00:35:15,180 --> 00:35:17,116
>> Mr. Nomiya.

589
00:35:17,182 --> 00:35:21,620
I'm glad I tested your reasoning skills.

590
00:35:21,687 --> 00:35:23,622
As expected.

591
00:35:23,689 --> 00:35:27,626
(Luna) After you're discharged from the hospital, let's join the mystery-solving circle again.

592
00:35:27,693 --> 00:35:31,129
>> That's great, please! Hahaha...

593
00:35:31,196 --> 00:35:36,635
Did you find the girl who came to the store?

594
00:35:36,702 --> 00:35:40,639
Yes, there is a copy of the license at the base of the special fraud→

595
00:35:40,706 --> 00:35:42,641
Found it right away.

596
00:35:42,708 --> 00:35:47,145
However, it is unclear whether he can be charged with a crime.

597
00:35:47,212 --> 00:35:49,648
is that so.

598
00:35:49,715 --> 00:35:52,651
(Luna) Thanks to the 10 yen.

599
00:35:52,718 --> 00:35:56,655
>> Hoho, did you see through that too?

600
00:35:56,722 --> 00:35:59,591
(Luna) She was the one who gave me the hint.

601
00:35:59,658 --> 00:36:04,596
Ryoko Sawatsuji is a friend who always helps me.

602
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:06,598
(Kurata) I see.

603
00:36:06,665 --> 00:36:10,602
Mr. Sawatsuji is Watson.

604
00:36:10,669 --> 00:36:12,604
(Ryoko) No, that's it.

605
00:36:12,671 --> 00:36:16,608
>> When I secured that female child →

606
00:36:16,675 --> 00:36:20,178
I handed you a receipt for 10 yen.

607
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:25,617
(Kurata's voice) That child is still young→

608
00:36:25,684 --> 00:36:28,620
I can't believe I'm trying my hand at a part-time job like this →

609
00:36:28,687 --> 00:36:34,126
I felt sorry for him, thinking there must be something serious going on.

610
00:36:34,192 --> 00:36:39,631
If she receives the cash, the crime of fraud will be established.

611
00:36:39,698 --> 00:36:44,636
So I decided to hand over “Hell Change” and “Kurotani Village” →

612
00:36:44,703 --> 00:36:47,205
I got an idea.

613
00:36:49,207 --> 00:36:53,145
(Kurata) [Because they didn't have cash available→

614
00:36:53,212 --> 00:36:57,149
Give this book to your friends.]

615
00:36:57,215 --> 00:37:01,587
[This will also sell for more than 1 million yen →

616
00:37:01,653 --> 00:37:04,156
I'm sure you'll agree.]

617
00:37:07,659 --> 00:37:10,596
[This is for you]

618
00:37:10,662 --> 00:37:14,666
[If you sell this too, it will be a good price]

619
00:37:16,168 --> 00:37:19,605
(Kurata) [Do you have any coins? Any amount is fine.]

620
00:37:19,671 --> 00:37:40,125
♪～

621
00:37:40,192 --> 00:37:42,127
[Okay? ]

622
00:37:42,194 --> 00:37:47,199
[You bought these three books]

623
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:51,637
How old is that child?

624
00:37:51,703 --> 00:37:53,639
I'm twenty years old.

625
00:37:53,705 --> 00:37:58,577
I'm with Sakura after all.

626
00:37:58,644 --> 00:38:02,581
When you look at young people of similar age →

627
00:38:02,648 --> 00:38:08,086
I overlapped with my daughter, son-in-law, and grandson.

628
00:38:08,153 --> 00:38:11,089
Sakura's mother is →

629
00:38:11,156 --> 00:38:14,593
Playing the violin in an orchestra →

630
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:19,097
Leave Sakura, who is still small, to her son-in-law →

631
00:38:19,164 --> 00:38:21,600
I was flying around all over the place.

632
00:38:21,667 --> 00:38:24,603
I looked at it→

633
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:28,607
I would rather stop playing music than leave my child behind →

634
00:38:28,674 --> 00:38:33,111
I denied my daughter's life.

635
00:38:33,178 --> 00:38:39,184
Since then, it has become insulated.

636
00:38:46,692 --> 00:38:51,697
(Kurata) I thought that I could meet you anytime if I felt like it.

637
00:38:53,699 --> 00:38:58,570
It's been 18 years since those kids died.

638
00:38:58,637 --> 00:39:04,643
The regret of not doing something will always remain.

639
00:39:06,645 --> 00:39:12,584
That's why I want to atone for my sins.

640
00:39:12,651 --> 00:39:16,588
I want to help young people.

641
00:39:16,655 --> 00:39:21,093
(Kurata) [In case I get arrested by the police→

642
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:25,597
Promptly show me the receipt.]

643
00:39:25,664 --> 00:39:30,669
[So don't do this again]

644
00:39:32,170 --> 00:39:34,106
[I see.]

645
00:39:34,172 --> 00:39:38,610
I understand how you feel, but unfortunately the world is...

646
00:39:38,677 --> 00:39:41,613
Most people are stubborn people who don't change their minds.

647
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:46,618
By now, that woman who was my child will also have the money from selling the book →

648
00:39:46,685 --> 00:39:49,121
You may be laughing out loud.

649
00:39:49,187 --> 00:39:58,563
♪～

650
00:39:58,630 --> 00:40:03,568
(Ryoko) Wow~ You can see the cherry blossoms from here too!

651
00:40:03,635 --> 00:40:08,073
>> Do you know why I like cherry blossom trees?

652
00:40:08,140 --> 00:40:11,576
(Ryoko) Hmm, is it because it's beautiful?

653
00:40:11,643 --> 00:40:15,080
>> It won't bloom unless it survives the winter.

654
00:40:15,147 --> 00:40:18,583
(Luna) Breaking dormancy. (Kurata) Yes.

655
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:23,588
This is when plants wake up from a dormant state and begin to grow.

656
00:40:23,655 --> 00:40:28,593
Cherry blossoms will not grow unless they survive the harsh cold.

657
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:33,165
So I guess humans are like that too.

658
00:40:35,167 --> 00:40:42,107
I think it's because people are in difficult situations that they can blossom someday.

659
00:40:42,174 --> 00:40:46,111
I just thought that.

660
00:40:46,178 --> 00:40:49,114
But in the end→

661
00:40:49,181 --> 00:40:53,185
Maybe it was my own satisfaction.

662
00:40:55,187 --> 00:41:00,125
(Luna) Why don't you ask him directly?

663
00:41:00,192 --> 00:41:10,135
♪～

664
00:41:10,202 --> 00:41:12,137
>>You...

665
00:41:12,204 --> 00:41:21,146
♪～

666
00:41:21,213 --> 00:41:23,148
You came well.

667
00:41:23,215 --> 00:41:37,162
♪～

668
00:41:37,229 --> 00:41:39,664
(Ryoko) Did you get the password?

669
00:41:39,731 --> 00:41:44,669
(Luna) I think I'll try using the publication date of the first edition first.

670
00:41:44,736 --> 00:42:00,619
♪～

671
00:42:00,685 --> 00:42:02,621
(Monitor) (Error sound)

672
00:42:02,687 --> 00:42:05,123
(Ryoko) Ah, no...

673
00:42:05,190 --> 00:42:08,693
What? Four more times?

674
00:42:11,696 --> 00:42:14,132
(Ryoko) Mom?

675
00:42:14,199 --> 00:42:17,636
(Luna) After all, I will return this computer to my mother.

676
00:42:17,702 --> 00:42:19,137
(Ryoko) Huh? Why?

677
00:42:19,204 --> 00:42:22,140
(Luna) It takes up a lot of my time and I don't feel at ease when I'm here.

678
00:42:22,207 --> 00:42:24,643
I've been busy this month.

679
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:29,147
(Ryoko) But didn't you ask me to open it?

680
00:42:29,214 --> 00:42:34,152
(Luna) I didn't say I would accept it, it was just forced on me unilaterally.

681
00:42:34,219 --> 00:42:36,655
(Ryoko) It has some meaning →

682
00:42:36,721 --> 00:42:40,225
I guess your mother entrusted it to you.

683
00:42:42,727 --> 00:42:47,666
I regretted ignoring Kazuto's answering machine.

684
00:42:47,732 --> 00:42:50,168
For over 20 years.

685
00:42:50,235 --> 00:42:52,671
Kurata-san also said that.

686
00:42:52,737 --> 00:42:56,741
The regret of not doing it will stay with me forever.

687
00:43:01,680 --> 00:43:03,615
(Sound of putting down computer)

688
00:43:03,682 --> 00:43:06,117
(Sound of leaving)

689
00:43:06,184 --> 00:43:08,186
(Ryoko) Huh…｡

690
00:43:12,691 --> 00:43:15,126
(Ryoko) What are you doing?

691
00:43:15,193 --> 00:43:19,130
(Luna) To Mr. Soseki's researcher who was introduced to me by Mr. Kurata→

692
00:43:19,197 --> 00:43:21,132
I'll try to make an appointment.

693
00:43:21,199 --> 00:43:23,635
(Ryoko) Wow, are you motivated?

694
00:43:23,702 --> 00:43:25,637
(Luna) Leaving unsolved mysteries as is →

695
00:43:25,704 --> 00:43:27,639
It's just disgusting.

696
00:43:27,706 --> 00:43:31,142
(Ryoko) Well then, I'll stay with you until the mystery is solved.

697
00:43:31,209 --> 00:43:35,213
If I leave mom alone, she might change her mind again.

698
00:43:36,715 --> 00:43:38,650
(Luna) Why so much?

699
00:43:38,717 --> 00:43:42,721
(Ryoko) Hmm... Is it because you have free time? Hehe.

700
00:43:46,725 --> 00:43:48,159
(Ryoko) I also once...

701
00:43:48,226 --> 00:43:51,162
⟨If you can open this computer→

702
00:43:51,229 --> 00:43:55,166
Mom's life homework may be solved ⟩

703
00:43:55,233 --> 00:43:59,604
⟨I want to be a good help even if I am nosy⟩

704
00:43:59,671 --> 00:44:05,110
⟨Just like my mom saved my heart in Osaka⟩

705
00:44:05,176 --> 00:44:07,112
I'm home~

706
00:44:07,178 --> 00:44:10,115
(Kikuo) \It's not a joke! >> What were you thinking! /

707
00:44:10,181 --> 00:44:12,117
(Aroma) \Don't make a loud noise! /

708
00:44:12,183 --> 00:44:14,119
(Kikuo) There's no way I'll forgive you!

709
00:44:14,185 --> 00:44:16,121
(Ryoko) What happened?

710
00:44:16,187 --> 00:44:19,624
>> Yoshika wants to quit university.

711
00:44:19,691 --> 00:44:21,126
(Ryoko) What!?

712
00:44:21,192 --> 00:44:24,629
>> Anyway, that's what it is!

713
00:44:24,696 --> 00:44:26,631
(Kikuo) Hey, Yoshika!

714
00:44:26,698 --> 00:44:36,141
♪～

715
00:44:36,207 --> 00:44:38,643
(Luna) Are you okay?

716
00:44:38,710 --> 00:44:44,716
♪～
